"{\"uid\": \"forbes.com-sites-hyunsoorim-2024-06-18-ralph-lauren-reveals-team-usas-uniforms-for-paris-2024-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByHyunsoo Rim,  Contributor.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 28, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ralph Laurenunveiledon Tuesday the opening and closing ceremony uniforms for Team USA athletes for the Paris 2024 Olympic and Paralympics, blending modern American style with classic designs and featuring the brand's first-ever \\\"100% recycled\\\" Polo shirt.\", \"from\": 30, \"to\": 285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 107, \"end\": 115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.8056917520873946, \"rank\": 0.2411399054798422, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 133, \"end\": 143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999941565, \"rank\": 5.847213855089183e-11, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 185, \"end\": 193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9917308632738894, \"rank\": 0.008329924496849776, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ralph Lauren is the official outfitter for Team USA for the ninth consecutive Olympics since2008, providing athletes uniforms for opening and closing ceremonies.\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 287, \"end\": 299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Lauren\", \"score\": 0.9987406498589385, \"rank\": 0.0012609381035674266, \"text\": \"Ralph Lauren\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Lauren\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Lauren\"}, {\"begin\": 330, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.8056917520873946, \"rank\": 0.2411399054798422, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the opening ceremony on July 26, Team USA athletes will wear a single-breasted navy wool blazer with red and white tipping, paired with a blue-and-white striped oxford shirt, tapered jeans, and a classic suede buck shoe, according to the company'sstatementreleased Tuesday.\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 486, \"end\": 494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.8056917520873946, \"rank\": 0.2411399054798422, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 614, \"end\": 626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dress_shirt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"oxford shirt\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dress_shirt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dress_shirt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The uniform for the closing ceremony on August 11 features a moto-style jacket with multiple patches, worn with white jeans and a classic striped Polo shirt.\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 874, \"end\": 884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polo_shirt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Polo shirt\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polo_shirt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polo_shirt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paralympic swimmer Jamal Hill described the closing ceremony outfit as combining \\\"cowboy tuxedo\\\" and Formula 1 style, while kiteboarder Daniela Moroz praised it as \\\"unique and cool,\\\"reportedUSA Today.\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 1087, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 887, \"end\": 905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para_swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympic swimmer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para_swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para_swimming\"}, {\"begin\": 906, \"end\": 911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamal_Lyon\", \"score\": 0.9998663238924365, \"rank\": 0.00012657849363744884, \"text\": \"Jamal\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamal_Lyon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamal_Lyon\"}, {\"begin\": 1023, \"end\": 1030, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\", \"score\": 0.98800330268058, \"rank\": 0.008111401832346198, \"text\": \"Daniela\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniela_Alves_Lima\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The athletes chosen as Team USA's flag bearers for the ceremony parades will weardistinctversions of these looks in alternate colorways to help them stand out, CNN reported.\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1112, \"end\": 1120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.8056917520873946, \"rank\": 0.2411399054798422, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1249, \"end\": 1252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 0.9999698993454931, \"rank\": 2.8496549961762918e-05, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 collection also includes a \\\"Villagewear\\\" collection that athletes can wear outside of official ceremonies, including sporty varsity jackets, rugby shirts, color-blocked tees, and a classic American flag sweater, the brand said in the statement.\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1268, \"end\": 1278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999941565, \"rank\": 5.847213855089183e-11, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1468, \"end\": 1481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999961346, \"rank\": 3.894929745752546e-12, \"text\": \"American flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The collection, as well as the opening and closing parade uniforms, are made with materials includingrecycledpolyester and USA-grown Responsible Wool Standard (RWS) certified wool, among other materials.\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1685, \"end\": 1688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RUAG\", \"score\": 0.5703170905556519, \"rank\": 0.7271484271421829, \"text\": \"RWS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RUAG\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RUAG\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ralph Lauren has been designing uniforms for Team USA since the2008Beijing Olympics.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1730, \"end\": 1742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Lauren\", \"score\": 0.9987406498589385, \"rank\": 0.0012609381035674266, \"text\": \"Ralph Lauren\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Lauren\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Lauren\"}, {\"begin\": 1775, \"end\": 1783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.8056917520873946, \"rank\": 0.2411399054798422, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the Paris 2024 Olympics, the company said it created outfits that \\\"draw inspiration from the dynamic and vibrant host city of Paris,\\\" as well as representing American culture and the spirit of Team USA-with a palette of red, white, and blue.\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 2060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1945, \"end\": 1950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999903443495, \"rank\": 9.655561723431424e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1977, \"end\": 1985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9917308632738894, \"rank\": 0.008329924496849776, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite past criticisms of the Tokyo 2020 Olympics uniform for exclusivity and a lack of diversity-with viewerscomparingthe athletes wearing uniforms to \\\"Karens\\\"-Ralph Laurenmaintainedits traditional approach.\", \"from\": 2061, \"to\": 2270, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The brand was directed to have the athletes look like ambassadors with a formal yet comfortable style, noted David Lauren, the chief branding and innovation officer of Ralph Lauren, to the New York Times.\", \"from\": 2271, \"to\": 2475, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2380, \"end\": 2392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Lauren\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Lauren\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Lauren\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Lauren\"}, {\"begin\": 2439, \"end\": 2451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Lauren\", \"score\": 0.9987406498589385, \"rank\": 0.0012609381035674266, \"text\": \"Ralph Lauren\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Lauren\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ralph_Lauren\"}, {\"begin\": 2460, \"end\": 2468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999998706193848, \"rank\": 7.562808909036742e-08, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}]}"